{"title_page": "Sabrina Scharf", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Sabrina Scharf\n| image = File:The Paradise Syndrome.jpg\n| caption = Scharf and [[William Shatner]] in \"[[The Paradise Syndrome]]\", 1968\n| birth_name    = Sandra Mae Trentman\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1943|10|17|mf=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Delphos, Ohio]], U.S.\n| death_date    = \n| death_place   =\n| spouse        = {{marriage|[[Bob Schiller]]|1969|2017|end=d.}} \n| children      = 2\n| occupation    = Actress\n| yearsactive   = 1965\u20131975\n}}\n\n'''Sabrina Scharf Schiller''' (born '''Sandra Mae Trentman''', October 17, 1943) is an American actress best known for her roles on American television shows. \n\nBorn in Delphos, Ohio, she moved with her mother to Arizona, eventually living in Tucson. She eloped with her algebra teacher at age 15. The marriage was annulled three years later. She later worked as a theatrical assistant in New York, then became a [[Playboy Bunny]] beginning in 1962.<ref name=\"delphos\">\"[https://delphosherald.com/Content/News/Community-News/Article/On-the-Banks-of-Yesteryear-To-boldly-go-Sabrina-Scharf-Schiller/191/1185/201975 On the Banks of Yesteryear \u2014 To boldly go\u2026 Sabrina Scharf Schiller].\" ''Delphos Herald'', February 18, 2017.</ref><ref>{{Cite book | url=https://books.google.com/?id=j5I62jQSEAIC&pg=PA136&lpg=PA136&dq=Sabrina+Scharf+children#v=onepage&q=Sabrina%20Scharf&f=false |title = The Bunny Years: The Surprising Inside Story of the Playboy Clubs: The Women Who Worked as Bunnies, and Where They Are Now|isbn = 9781451663280|last1 = Scott|first1 = Kathryn Leigh|date = September 27, 2011}}</ref> She appeared in the movie ''[[Easy Rider]]'' and guest-starred in the third season episode of the original ''[[Star Trek: The Original Series|Star Trek]]'', [[The Paradise Syndrome]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=cbYf2l7gczUC&pg=PT1196&lpg=PT1196&dq=Sabrina+Scharf+star+trek+Encyclopedia&source=bl&ots=lFtJJ1m-Vu&sig=h1MaA3sRdIiE9kCoaYv78563OBo&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjUy9H0n_bQAhXpyVQKHUrMCDIQ6AEIMTAD#v=onepage&q=Sabrina%20Scharf%20star%20trek%20Encyclopedia&f=false The Star Trek Encyclopedia by Michael Okuda, Denise Okuda, and Debbie Mirek]</ref>\n\nAfter Scharf quit acting in the 1970s, she became an anti-pollution activist and unsuccessfully ran for the [[California State Senate]]. She was married to television writer [[Bob Schiller]] until his death in 2017.<ref>Stammer, Larry B. (1986). [http://articles.latimes.com/1986-07-01/local/me-630_1_clean-air \"Sabrina Schiller--Her Crusade for Clean Air Creates a Whirlwind\"], ''Los Angeles Times'', Los Angeles, California, July 1, 1986. Retrieved June 12, 2018.</ref>\n\nSabrina Scharf Schiller became an attorney in 1989.<ref>http://lawyers-usa.org/c-1042311-sabrina-scharf-schiller.html</ref> As of 2017 she works in real estate in the Los Angeles area.<ref name=\"delphos\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Films===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|1966|| ''[[Dead Heat on a Merry-Go-Round]]'' || Girl in Bed with Eli || Uncredited\n|-\n|1967|| ''[[Hells Angels on Wheels]]'' || Shill ||\n|-\n|1967|| ''[[Waterhole No. 3]]'' || Dove || Uncredited\n|-\n|1969|| ''[[Easy Rider]]'' || Sarah ||\n|-\n|1969|| ''The Virgin President'' || President's girlfriend ||\n|-\n|1973|| ''[[Hunter (1973 film)|Hunter]]'' || Anne Novak || TV Movie\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|1965|| ''[[Gidget (TV series)|Gidget]]'' || Penelope Peterson || 1 episode\n|-\n|1966|| ''[[The Man from U.N.C.L.E.]]'' || Mari Brooks || 1 episode\n|-\n|1966|| ''[[The Girl from U.N.C.L.E.]]'' || Greta Wolfe || 1 episode\n|-\n|1966|| ''[[Daniel Boone (1964  TV series)|Daniel Boone]]'' || Alkini Matthews || 1 episode\n|-\n|1967|| ''[[Captain Nice]]'' || Miss Schneider || 1 episode\n|-\n|1968|| ''[[The Wild Wild West]]'' || China Hazard || 1 episode\n|-\n|1968|| ''[